Package: qgg
Type: Package
Title: Statistical tools for Quantitative Genetic Analyses
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2019-09-01
Authors@R: c(person("Peter", "Soerensen", email = "pso@mbg.au.dk",
                  role = c("aut", "cre")),
                  person("Palle", "Duun Rohde", email = "palle.d.rohde@mbg.au.dk",
                  role = "aut"),
                  person("Izel", "Fourie Soerensen", email = "izel.sorensen@gmail.com",
                  role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Peter Soerensen <pso@mbg.au.dk>
Description: Statistical tools for quantitative genetic analyses. 
   The qgg package provides an infrastructure for efficient processing of large-scale genetic and phenotypic data including core functions for: 
   1) fitting linear mixed models, 2) constructing marker-based genomic relationship matrices, 3) estimating genetic parameters (heritability and correlation), 
   4) performing genomic prediction and genetic risk profiling, and 5) single or multi-marker association analyses
   Rohde et al. (2019) <doi:10.1101/503631>.
   Soerensen et al. (2016) <doi:10.1038/s41598-017-02281-3>.
   Rohde et al. (2016) <doi:10.1534/genetics.116.189498>.
   Edwards et al. (2016) <doi:10.1534/genetics.116.187161>.
